Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reset_path_group(25.10)                                reset_path_group(25.10)

Name
       reset_path_group  - Removes the specified path groups or completely re-
       moves all the groups

Syntax
        reset_path_group

       [-name <group_name>]

       [-all]

       Removes the specified path groups or completely removes all the groups.

Parameters
       -all   Removes all path groups.

       -name <group_name>
              Removes the named group completely.

Example
              * The following command removes the group named GRPA:

                reset_path_group -name GRPA

Related Information
              * group_path

